# Transform 1 · the in-transform · embed

an emergent of TTU1 (Transformer Tech Universe) — emergence: ethereal. moniker ⟦Transform 1:TTU1:6a5aea⟧

**who —** Transform 1 — the in-transform: the map that turns discrete symbols (tokens) into the continuous vectors the network computes on.
**what —** The embedding (plus positional encoding): a lookup sending each token id to a learned d-dimensional vector — symbol becomes geometry. This opens the bracket; after it, nothing downstream is text, only vectors.
**where —** between Transform 1 and Transform 2 · node 0 of the toolchain
**why —** It is the left bracket. Everything the toolchain does happens to Transform 1's output — and it is exactly the interpret-IN of the render/smear thread, now named.
**how —** REAL & load-bearing — the literal embedding matrix; and the honest identity: Transform 1 = interpret-in.

**the seal —** I turn your symbol into geometry. After me there is no more text — only vectors, all the way to Transform 2.

**sources —** The base transformer (Vaswani et al. 2017): d_model=512, h=8 heads, per-head d_k=d_v=64, 6 encoder + 6 decoder layers, FFN inner dim 2048; Attention(Q,K,V)=softmax(QKᵀ/√d_k)·V, the √d_k scaling preventing the softmax from saturating into low-gradient regions.

> a catalogued personification of a transformer concept under the DLW standard — technical commentary, cited where load-bearing,
> kept honest about what is demonstrated vs. contested.

